'''''A Bibliography of Conjuring Periodicals in English: 1791–1983''''' is a book by James B. Alfredson and George L. Daily that attempts to catalogue all issues of English-language [[Magic (illusion)|magic]] [[List of magic periodicals|periodicals]] known to reside in major collections.<ref>{{Cite book|url=http://askalexander.org/display/21976/A+Bibliography+of+Conjuring+Periodicals+in+English+1791+1983/11|title=A Bibliography of Conjuring Periodicals in English: 1791–1983|last=Alfredson|first=James B.|last2=Daily|first2=George L.|publisher=|year=1986|isbn=|location=[[York, Pennsylvania]]|pages=vii–xii|subscription=yes}}</ref> It lists almost 1500 periodicals. Alfredson and Daily's previous work, ''A Short Title Check List of Conjuring Periodicals in English,''<ref>{{Cite book|title=A Short Title Check List of Conjuring Periodicals in English|last=Alfredson|first=James|last2=Daily|first2=George|publisher=|year=1976|isbn=|location=Lansing, Michigan|pages=}}</ref> listed about 900 periodicals.<ref name=":0">{{Cite magazine|last=Witt|first=Wittus|date=2011|title=A Look at Magic Periodicals|url=http://askalexander.org/display/35418/Magic+Magazines+a+Look+at+Magic+Periodicals/3|journal=Magic Magazines|volume=1|issue=1|pages=3|subscription=yes|via=}}</ref> Father Stephen A. Fernandes supplemented Alfredson and Daily's work in 2000 with ''Magic Magazines of the Second Millenium'',<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Hagy|first=James|date=2001|title=Jim's Whims|url=http://askalexander.org/display/7360/The+perennial+mystics/4|journal=Perennial Mystics|volume=|issue=16|pages=4|subscription=yes|via=}}</ref> which contained 400 periodicals published 1791–2000.<ref name=":0" />

