{{italic title}} {{for|the historical fort sometimes called Fort Wheeling|Fort Henry (West Virginia)}} [[Image:Pratt-fortwheeling.jpg|thumb|right|300px|''Wheeling'' on the front page of ''Misterix'' no. 700 (1962)]] '''''Fort Wheeling''''', or simply '''''Wheeling''''', is the title of a [[comics|comics series]] set in [[colonial North America]], by [[Italy|Italian]] [[comic book creator|comics creator]] [[Hugo Pratt]].
==Publication history== ''Wheeling'' first appeared in the [[Argentina|Argentine]] comics magazine ''Misterix'' in 1962.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Historieteca.com|title=Misterix, la revista|url=http://www.historieteca.com.ar/Revistas/misterix_la_revista.htm|language=Spanish}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Dreamers.com|title=Cronologia completa de Hugo Pratt|url=http://dreamers.com/corto/cronolo.html|language=Spanish}}</ref> The series has since 1972 been reprinted in several editions, among these collections by publishers [[Florenzo Ivaldi]], [[Casterman]] and [[Les Humanoïdes Associés]].
==Synopsis== Patrick Fitzgerald, aristocrat, and Chris Kenton, Virginian, are young soldiers serving on the frontier of Great Britain's American colonies just prior to the [[American Revolution]]. During the French and Indian war they fall in love with the beautiful Mohena, a captive rescued from the [[Shawnee]] Indians. When the American Revolution begins, however, the two friends choose different sides.
