'''Invictus Games''' is an independent Hungarian video game development studio founded in 2000 by Tamás Kozák and Ákos Diviánszky. They specialize in racing simulation games, like ''[[Project Torque]]'', ''[[Street Legal (game)|Street Legal]]'' and ''[[Street Legal Racing Redline]]'', and ''[[Insane (2001 video game)|Insane]]''. They also developed ''[[onEscapee]]'', a cinematic platforming game. Their publishers include [[Codemasters]], [[Activision]], [[1C]], [[Gamepot]] and Joyzone.

==External links==
